1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:01:02,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:01:19,184 --> 00:01:20,101
Se-ah.

3
00:01:20,185 --> 00:01:24,856
IF WISHES COULD KILL

4
00:01:37,076 --> 00:01:39,329
I'm okay.

5
00:01:54,093 --> 00:01:56,596
There was another person?

6
00:01:57,096 --> 00:01:58,097
Yes.

7
00:01:59,057 --> 00:02:01,392
I was so scared that I woke up right away,

8
00:02:02,060 --> 00:02:04,437
but there was one in front of me
and one behind me.

9
00:02:04,520 --> 00:02:08,107
So does that mean there could've been
more than one person?

10
00:02:09,234 --> 00:02:10,902
Got the knife and spirit compass?

11
00:02:14,614 --> 00:02:16,866
With this,
they won't be able to touch you.

12
00:02:16,950 --> 00:02:19,369
But if it breaks,
you must return immediately.

13
00:02:19,452 --> 00:02:20,286
Okay.

14
00:02:20,370 --> 00:02:23,122
And if the timer starts again,
come back immediately.

15
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:29,045
Don't answer any calls on your phone.
Ignore all text messages too.

16
00:02:29,128 --> 00:02:32,632
If I need to, I'll reach you
through Bangwool or Ha-joon.

17
00:02:33,132 --> 00:02:35,134
You're still the same. Always nagging.

18
00:02:38,304 --> 00:02:41,349
I mean, stop worrying already.

19
00:02:42,058 --> 00:02:43,601
You do nag a lot.

20
00:02:45,186 --> 00:02:46,521
That's why I like you.

21
00:02:47,981 --> 00:02:49,482
Take good care of the kids.

22
00:02:50,608 --> 00:02:51,484
Don't worry.

23
00:02:51,567 --> 00:02:55,738
No matter what happens, I'll make sure
not a hair on their heads is harmed.

24
00:02:56,239 --> 00:02:57,782
Okay? Don't you worry.

25
00:03:05,790 --> 00:03:06,666
We'll be back.

26
00:03:25,351 --> 00:03:27,103
What is it? Did you forget something?

27
00:03:28,354 --> 00:03:29,188
Well,

28
00:03:29,981 --> 00:03:30,982
thanks.

29
00:03:32,608 --> 00:03:34,193
I'm thanking you for helping us.

30
00:03:34,777 --> 00:03:37,530
And while we're out,
make sure to take care of your injuries.

31
00:03:53,921 --> 00:03:57,884
So Ha-young can't leave the house
at all, right?

32
00:03:57,967 --> 00:03:59,177
No.

33
00:03:59,761 --> 00:04:01,012
If she left the house,

34
00:04:01,929 --> 00:04:04,057
her body couldn't handle it. That's why.

35
00:04:04,766 --> 00:04:06,684
Is she sick?

36
00:04:06,768 --> 00:04:09,771
Not exactly. How should I explain this?

37
00:04:09,854 --> 00:04:10,688
Let's see.

38
00:04:12,148 --> 00:04:13,149
I don't care why.

39
00:04:13,941 --> 00:04:17,362
For the rest of her life,
she won't be able to leave that house?

40
00:04:18,071 --> 00:04:19,155
Just answer that.

41
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:24,494
I'll find a way for her to get out,
no matter what.

42
00:04:24,577 --> 00:04:27,830
I'll do whatever it takes.

43
00:04:39,384 --> 00:04:42,428
GOODBYE
FROM SEORIN-SI

44
00:04:49,394 --> 00:04:50,520
Hello.

45
00:04:51,020 --> 00:04:52,146
Hello.

46
00:05:22,927 --> 00:05:25,096
Hey, what are you doing here?

47
00:05:25,972 --> 00:05:28,015
Se-ah's aunt asked me to run an errand.

48
00:05:28,516 --> 00:05:29,934
What about you?

49
00:05:30,017 --> 00:05:31,727
Let's talk inside.

50
00:05:40,111 --> 00:05:44,282
REPAIR COMPLETE

51
00:05:50,371 --> 00:05:51,456
HAPPY BIRTHDAY

52
00:05:51,539 --> 00:05:53,708
How about fixing this for my birthday?

53
00:05:53,791 --> 00:05:54,917
I told you I'm busy.

54
00:05:55,001 --> 00:05:56,002
The PIN is the same.

55
00:06:22,778 --> 00:06:23,946
What are you doing?

56
00:06:24,030 --> 00:06:26,699
I feel bad for Hyeong-wook,
but I'll check everything.

57
00:06:26,782 --> 00:06:31,329
His browser history, cookies, cache, logs,
messages, and even hidden temp files

58
00:06:31,412 --> 00:06:33,748
to see how he found out about Girigo.

59
00:06:33,831 --> 00:06:36,000
His phone is synced to his Google account,

60
00:06:36,083 --> 00:06:39,921
so I can see what he searched
and which sites he visited on his phone.

61
00:06:40,004 --> 00:06:42,590
I don't follow,
but this will take a while, huh?

62
00:06:42,673 --> 00:06:44,133
No, it will be quick.

63
00:06:44,217 --> 00:06:45,760
I'm only checking June 2.

64
00:06:46,928 --> 00:06:49,514
-The day before the math exam?
-Yeah.

65
00:06:50,097 --> 00:06:53,142
Hyeong-wook was so stressed about studying
that he even took meds.

66
00:06:54,060 --> 00:06:56,729
Even so, since he never spent money
on games…

67
00:06:56,812 --> 00:06:58,773
Whether he believed in Girigo or not,

68
00:06:59,524 --> 00:07:02,276
he would've tried every last thing
before making the wish.

69
00:07:03,319 --> 00:07:04,153
Yeah.

70
00:07:06,072 --> 00:07:10,117
Nothing special the day before the exam.
He was just on Discord a lot.

71
00:07:10,201 --> 00:07:11,661
He was doing a lot of disco?

72
00:07:16,374 --> 00:07:17,208
Discord.

73
00:07:17,291 --> 00:07:18,793
Basically, it's a social platform

74
00:07:18,876 --> 00:07:23,172
that combines screen sharing, messaging,
voice chat, and forums in one place.

75
00:07:24,423 --> 00:07:26,592
Huh? What do I do?

76
00:07:28,386 --> 00:07:30,513
Let's answer it. With the mic off.

77
00:07:31,847 --> 00:07:32,932
OGRE MIN-SOO-SAN

78
00:07:33,015 --> 00:07:35,017
Choi Hyeong-wook,
what the fuck is going on?

79
00:07:35,101 --> 00:07:36,352
I've been shitting myself!

80
00:07:36,435 --> 00:07:37,270
You know him?

81
00:07:37,353 --> 00:07:39,897
Why aren't you answering me?
If you picked up, say something!

82
00:07:41,524 --> 00:07:42,650
Hello?

83
00:07:43,401 --> 00:07:44,235
Choi Hyeong-wook?

84
00:07:47,947 --> 00:07:49,115
You're not him, are you?

85
00:07:50,408 --> 00:07:51,576
Who are you?

86
00:07:52,660 --> 00:07:53,578
Gomen!

87
00:07:55,246 --> 00:07:56,330
I can't use the mic.

88
00:08:03,588 --> 00:08:05,047
Where are you? The study room?

89
00:08:05,131 --> 00:08:07,800
Damn, you're studying your ass off.
What, shooting for SNU?

90
00:08:07,883 --> 00:08:09,343
But why were you so scared?

91
00:08:09,844 --> 00:08:10,886
Somethin' up?

92
00:08:14,974 --> 00:08:19,270
There's a rumor going around
that you're dead, dumbass!

93
00:08:19,770 --> 00:08:21,522
Man, I almost felt bad for you.

94
00:08:24,275 --> 00:08:25,693
Why would he feel bad?

95
00:08:28,446 --> 00:08:30,448
This punk knows what Girigo is.

96
00:08:33,993 --> 00:08:35,202
Is that why you called me?

97
00:08:35,703 --> 00:08:37,705
Scared I'd come back as a ghost
to haunt you?

98
00:08:37,788 --> 00:08:39,206
To see if I'm still alive?

99
00:08:39,290 --> 00:08:40,541
That's not it, man.

100
00:08:40,625 --> 00:08:43,169
Remember what you asked me
to get you last time?

101
00:08:43,252 --> 00:08:44,086
I got it.

102
00:08:44,170 --> 00:08:46,464
What now? You want it?

103
00:08:47,965 --> 00:08:49,634
Fufufu, that would be great.

104
00:08:49,717 --> 00:08:50,801
How about now?

105
00:08:57,141 --> 00:08:58,225
Now?

106
00:09:04,148 --> 00:09:07,276
In that case,
I'll see you there in an hour. That spot.

107
00:09:09,236 --> 00:09:10,279
Where is that spot?

108
00:09:12,365 --> 00:09:13,824
You guys don't know? Oh man.

109
00:09:16,160 --> 00:09:16,994
What now?

110
00:09:20,498 --> 00:09:21,582
Hold on a second.

111
00:09:23,209 --> 00:09:25,920
Hyeong-wook's phone is synced
with his Google account,

112
00:09:26,003 --> 00:09:27,546
so I can see his past routes.

113
00:09:30,508 --> 00:09:33,636
From what he said,
it sounds like they met up a lot lately.

114
00:09:33,719 --> 00:09:35,471
It must be a spot that shows up a lot.

115
00:09:35,554 --> 00:09:36,847
"Baekun Middle School"?

116
00:09:54,073 --> 00:09:55,199
Sorry, one sec.

117
00:09:58,077 --> 00:09:59,954
The phone's not gonna magically appear.

118
00:10:00,037 --> 00:10:02,707
You've already checked this spot
three times.

119
00:10:02,790 --> 00:10:05,126
If you still can't find it,
it's probably not here.

120
00:10:06,877 --> 00:10:08,629
Na-ri, let me use your phone.

121
00:10:08,713 --> 00:10:11,382
You don't even know
what you might find in my photos.

122
00:10:11,465 --> 00:10:13,467
I just wanna watch
the video you took again.

123
00:10:13,968 --> 00:10:16,887
I think it might have captured
where my phone flew off.

124
00:10:18,305 --> 00:10:19,682
And here I was thinking…

125
00:10:21,517 --> 00:10:23,936
Just saying,
but don't look at anything else.

126
00:10:24,019 --> 00:10:25,020
All right.

127
00:10:51,547 --> 00:10:52,715
Se-ah.

128
00:11:04,435 --> 00:11:07,104
If you're gonna do that all day,
I'm going home.

129
00:11:07,188 --> 00:11:08,063
Give me my phone.

130
00:11:11,317 --> 00:11:13,736
It's about time he showed up.

131
00:11:13,819 --> 00:11:15,905
It's been an hour.

132
00:11:16,947 --> 00:11:17,990
This won't do.

133
00:11:21,494 --> 00:11:22,828
Show up!

134
00:11:24,413 --> 00:11:25,414
That didn't work.

135
00:11:27,166 --> 00:11:28,167
Watch closely.

136
00:11:30,044 --> 00:11:31,253
Show up!

137
00:11:34,048 --> 00:11:35,049
Look, he's here.

138
00:11:36,550 --> 00:11:37,384
It's him.

139
00:11:37,468 --> 00:11:38,469
I'll be right back.

140
00:11:38,552 --> 00:11:39,553
You must bring him.

141
00:11:39,637 --> 00:11:41,597
-You know that, right?
-Yeah.

142
00:11:47,436 --> 00:11:49,146
Man, I don't know about this.

143
00:11:50,022 --> 00:11:51,148
To be honest, me too.

144
00:11:55,778 --> 00:11:58,322
Now where was that bus stop again?

145
00:12:03,244 --> 00:12:05,746
I mean, the bus stop…

146
00:12:09,708 --> 00:12:11,460
The bus stop should be…

147
00:12:11,961 --> 00:12:13,087
Not interested.

148
00:12:13,879 --> 00:12:14,964
-What?
-You heard me.

149
00:12:15,047 --> 00:12:15,881
No, I was just--

150
00:12:15,965 --> 00:12:19,844
So many people who really need help suffer
because of people like you!

151
00:12:19,927 --> 00:12:23,222
How can someone trying to spread
their religion start with a lie?

152
00:12:23,305 --> 00:12:24,765
This guy is unbelievable.

153
00:12:27,810 --> 00:12:28,686
Ogre Min-soo-san?

154
00:12:28,769 --> 00:12:30,187
-Yeah. Wait, huh?
-Huh?

155
00:12:32,481 --> 00:12:33,941
So it is you, you punk.

156
00:12:36,861 --> 00:12:37,736
Huh?

157
00:12:42,658 --> 00:12:43,576
Hey, you punk!

158
00:12:45,619 --> 00:12:47,037
Hey! Get him!

159
00:12:48,873 --> 00:12:50,624
Hey! Stop right there!

160
00:12:56,463 --> 00:12:58,340
Why are they chasing me?

161
00:13:00,009 --> 00:13:02,553
Hey, you punk! Why are you running away?

162
00:13:04,430 --> 00:13:06,807
-If you can't keep up, stay here.
-Just go, hurry!

163
00:13:19,862 --> 00:13:21,780
Hey, I said stop!

164
00:13:39,548 --> 00:13:41,425
Hey, why would you even go up there?

165
00:13:41,508 --> 00:13:44,094
Then why the hell are you chasing me?

166
00:13:44,178 --> 00:13:45,429
Son of a…

167
00:13:47,097 --> 00:13:49,266
-What about Se-ah?
-No idea. She's gone.

168
00:13:49,350 --> 00:13:50,684
I think we lost her.

169
00:14:00,903 --> 00:14:01,737
Hey!

170
00:14:08,494 --> 00:14:09,578
Where are they?

171
00:14:20,339 --> 00:14:21,757
Damn it.

172
00:14:31,350 --> 00:14:32,351
For the love of…

173
00:14:35,396 --> 00:14:37,189
-Hey.
-Go home.

174
00:14:37,856 --> 00:14:39,108
I told you to go home!

175
00:14:39,191 --> 00:14:40,734
I told you to stop.

176
00:14:52,371 --> 00:14:53,372
Huh?

177
00:15:06,176 --> 00:15:07,553
Was that Se-ah?

178
00:15:07,636 --> 00:15:09,096
Hurry! To the rooftop!

179
00:15:13,225 --> 00:15:15,227
That really hurts.

180
00:15:17,813 --> 00:15:18,647
Hey.

181
00:15:19,690 --> 00:15:21,191
I told you to stop, didn't I?

182
00:15:21,275 --> 00:15:22,776
What even are you?

183
00:15:23,444 --> 00:15:24,611
What are you?

184
00:15:25,988 --> 00:15:30,034
-Been to Hyeong-wook's birthday party?
-Party? We're not fucking kids.

185
00:15:30,117 --> 00:15:32,119
I guess you're not close to Hyeong-wook.

186
00:15:36,915 --> 00:15:38,459
What did you do to Hyeong-wook?

187
00:15:38,542 --> 00:15:41,086
I believe in gender equality!

188
00:15:41,170 --> 00:15:44,965
Even with girls,
I can hit them like this! Like this!

189
00:15:45,049 --> 00:15:46,717
What the fuck did you do to him?

190
00:15:50,804 --> 00:15:52,056
Se-ah, are you all right?

191
00:15:52,139 --> 00:15:52,973
Yeah, I'm okay.

192
00:15:53,057 --> 00:15:54,308
-You're not hurt?
-No.

193
00:15:55,142 --> 00:15:57,061
Are you okay? Where is that punk?

194
00:15:57,144 --> 00:15:58,228
Over there.

195
00:15:58,312 --> 00:16:00,189
What's wrong with him? Did you do this?

196
00:16:00,272 --> 00:16:01,398
No.

197
00:16:02,649 --> 00:16:03,484
Hey.

198
00:16:04,109 --> 00:16:04,943
Hey.

199
00:16:05,027 --> 00:16:05,903
Oh, he's fine.

200
00:16:06,403 --> 00:16:07,404
Look at me.

201
00:16:07,488 --> 00:16:08,781
Look at me.

202
00:16:09,907 --> 00:16:11,533
I'm not a cult member.

203
00:16:12,743 --> 00:16:13,577
Okay?

204
00:16:16,246 --> 00:16:19,208
So Hyeong-wook reached out first
and asked for this?

205
00:16:19,291 --> 00:16:20,125
Yes, sir.

206
00:16:21,877 --> 00:16:23,420
I'm not a drug dealer or anything.

207
00:16:23,504 --> 00:16:25,422
Hyeong-wook said he was struggling

208
00:16:25,506 --> 00:16:28,217
because the side effects from his meds
made his heart race.

209
00:16:28,300 --> 00:16:31,512
I was trying to give him
the meds I use for side effects.

210
00:16:31,595 --> 00:16:33,222
Then why'd you run when you saw me?

211
00:16:34,056 --> 00:16:35,516
I came to meet Hyeong-wook.

212
00:16:35,599 --> 00:16:38,060
Of course I'd run
if some weird guy kept talking to me.

213
00:16:38,143 --> 00:16:39,561
-Me?
-No, sir.

214
00:16:39,645 --> 00:16:42,523
So you met Hyeong-wook on Discord?

215
00:16:43,565 --> 00:16:45,567
And you sent him the Girigo link?

216
00:16:51,490 --> 00:16:52,574
Why did you send it?

217
00:16:54,076 --> 00:16:55,828
So he'd make a wish and die?

218
00:16:55,911 --> 00:16:57,955
We're the ones you chatted with earlier.

219
00:17:00,124 --> 00:17:01,125
Hyeong-wook…

220
00:17:03,710 --> 00:17:05,295
Hyeong-wook is dead.

221
00:17:08,298 --> 00:17:09,925
Stop pretending to be shocked!

222
00:17:10,425 --> 00:17:13,637
You knew he would die too.
That's why you were shitting yourself!

223
00:17:19,393 --> 00:17:20,811
Hyeong-wook also saw the post.

224
00:17:21,395 --> 00:17:23,021
He didn't read it properly.

225
00:17:23,105 --> 00:17:26,024
-It was all written there.
-What post?

226
00:17:26,608 --> 00:17:28,569
The post. I'll show you.

227
00:17:30,988 --> 00:17:31,822
The post…

228
00:17:35,242 --> 00:17:36,368
It's been deleted.

229
00:17:36,451 --> 00:17:38,287
-Hey.
-Wait. Only the content's gone.

230
00:17:38,370 --> 00:17:39,538
-Let me…
-Messing with us?

231
00:17:39,621 --> 00:17:42,332
-Give me your phone.
-Let me try it now.

232
00:17:46,879 --> 00:17:48,630
"Seorin High ghost story"?

233
00:17:48,714 --> 00:17:49,882
Hyeong-wook

234
00:17:51,341 --> 00:17:53,844
was really excited
since it was about his school.

235
00:17:53,927 --> 00:17:57,347
Did this post mention what happens
if the wish is granted?

236
00:18:01,643 --> 00:18:04,188
It might've been there, or it might not--

237
00:18:04,271 --> 00:18:05,105
Hey.

238
00:18:06,773 --> 00:18:07,691
Say it straight.

239
00:18:07,774 --> 00:18:09,902
I really don't remember!

240
00:18:09,985 --> 00:18:12,613
It's all we talked about
when we chatted on Discord.

241
00:18:12,696 --> 00:18:15,532
How am I supposed to remember all of that?

242
00:18:15,616 --> 00:18:19,036
I wasn't as close to him as you guys,
but I was his friend too.

243
00:18:19,620 --> 00:18:23,540
At least on Discord,
I was his best friend.

244
00:18:26,043 --> 00:18:27,044
What's this rule?

245
00:18:27,127 --> 00:18:28,295
The post removal rules.

246
00:18:28,378 --> 00:18:29,880
POST HAS BEEN REMOVED
DUE TO A VIOLATION

247
00:18:29,963 --> 00:18:31,965
Must be the name and picture.

248
00:18:32,049 --> 00:18:33,425
No, I'm sure of it.

249
00:18:33,508 --> 00:18:36,553
It's a violation
if even one of them is in a post.

250
00:18:36,637 --> 00:18:41,934
That post had both names and a photo,
so I remember thinking it was risky.

251
00:18:42,768 --> 00:18:44,561
Well, that's what made it more fun.

252
00:18:45,187 --> 00:18:46,855
Do you remember the names?

253
00:18:47,564 --> 00:18:48,899
Kwon Si-won, Do Hye-ryung.

254
00:18:48,982 --> 00:18:51,318
You said you didn't remember the contents,

255
00:18:51,401 --> 00:18:53,487
but you remember the exact names.

256
00:18:53,570 --> 00:18:55,239
At our school, everyone knew

257
00:18:56,406 --> 00:18:58,784
there was a crazy shaman's daughter
at Baekun.

258
00:18:58,867 --> 00:19:00,244
A shaman's daughter?

259
00:19:00,327 --> 00:19:01,203
Yes, sir.

260
00:19:01,286 --> 00:19:02,996
You said there was a photo too?

261
00:19:03,580 --> 00:19:04,998
If what you say is true,

262
00:19:05,082 --> 00:19:07,751
there should be a cached image
on Hyeong-wook's laptop.

263
00:19:18,845 --> 00:19:20,681
-I'm sorry.
-No, I'm fine.

264
00:19:20,764 --> 00:19:22,599
Is this the photo from the post?

265
00:19:24,101 --> 00:19:25,185
It is.

266
00:19:25,686 --> 00:19:26,979
On the left, Kwon Si-won.

267
00:19:27,062 --> 00:19:29,106
Right, Do Hye-ryung,
the shaman's daughter.

268
00:19:30,816 --> 00:19:31,984
KANG HA-YOUNG

269
00:19:32,484 --> 00:19:34,069
FILE TRANSFER

270
00:19:38,365 --> 00:19:39,533
No need to be scared.

271
00:19:40,575 --> 00:19:41,785
Where's the shaman's home?

272
00:19:44,329 --> 00:19:47,040
I'm asking where Do Hye-ryung lives.
You don't know?

273
00:19:47,916 --> 00:19:49,209
I do know the neighborhood.

274
00:19:51,962 --> 00:19:54,381
I'll report you to the police!
I hope your tires…

275
00:19:59,344 --> 00:20:01,930
He wasn't lying. That's for sure.

276
00:20:02,014 --> 00:20:05,100
Se-ah, you said you saw
two female students in your dream, right?

277
00:20:05,684 --> 00:20:06,560
Yes.

278
00:20:06,643 --> 00:20:08,937
It was so quick I barely saw their faces,

279
00:20:09,438 --> 00:20:10,480
but there were two.

280
00:20:10,564 --> 00:20:14,818
We're heading to the neighborhood
where Do Hye-ryung lived.

281
00:20:14,901 --> 00:20:18,113
I'll call you right away if we go there
and find or learn anything.

282
00:20:18,196 --> 00:20:20,240
Okay. Be careful, all of you.

283
00:20:20,324 --> 00:20:21,950
Okay. Don't worry too much.

284
00:20:34,421 --> 00:20:37,674
Why did it go out of its way
to come all the way in here?

285
00:21:11,124 --> 00:21:13,001
Here, take a look.

286
00:21:13,502 --> 00:21:16,713
On the gates or somewhere high enough
to be seen from outside,

287
00:21:16,797 --> 00:21:19,674
you'll see flags or symbols like these.

288
00:21:20,717 --> 00:21:21,802
Like this.

289
00:21:21,885 --> 00:21:23,136
Just like this.

290
00:21:23,720 --> 00:21:27,015
If you see houses like this,
don't just go in.

291
00:21:27,099 --> 00:21:28,433
Tell me right away.

292
00:21:29,142 --> 00:21:30,060
-Okay?
-Okay.

293
00:21:30,143 --> 00:21:31,228
All right.

294
00:21:32,312 --> 00:21:33,397
Let's go!

295
00:21:33,480 --> 00:21:34,314
Seriously.

296
00:21:37,401 --> 00:21:38,568
Let's go that way.

297
00:21:45,534 --> 00:21:46,660
This way.

298
00:21:46,743 --> 00:21:47,953
That way.

299
00:21:48,537 --> 00:21:49,955
Do you know where you're going?

300
00:21:52,165 --> 00:21:53,208
Hold on just a second.

301
00:21:54,751 --> 00:21:57,170
The sun will set
by the time we get to the top.

302
00:21:57,254 --> 00:21:59,464
Are we really
just wandering around clueless?

303
00:22:00,173 --> 00:22:01,007
Are you tired?

304
00:22:01,508 --> 00:22:04,344
-I'm sorry.
-No, that's not what I meant.

305
00:22:04,928 --> 00:22:07,722
I just thought it would be harder
to search once the sun sets,

306
00:22:08,306 --> 00:22:10,100
so it might be better to split up--

307
00:22:10,183 --> 00:22:12,769
That's the reason
we're trying to get to the top.

308
00:22:13,270 --> 00:22:15,063
What are you talking about?

309
00:22:15,689 --> 00:22:17,190
Just trust your brother-in-law.

310
00:22:17,274 --> 00:22:18,316
Let's go!

311
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:19,484
I'll push you.

312
00:22:19,568 --> 00:22:20,610
No, I'm good.

313
00:22:22,404 --> 00:22:24,656
Brother-in-law, you've got this!

314
00:22:39,421 --> 00:22:40,672
-Huh?
-Huh?

315
00:22:40,755 --> 00:22:42,466
There's a house with the lights on.

316
00:22:43,091 --> 00:22:44,301
Okay, we found it.

317
00:22:47,304 --> 00:22:49,181
CORNER STORE

318
00:22:49,264 --> 00:22:51,057
Hello, ma'am.

319
00:22:52,809 --> 00:22:54,561
Hello, ma'am.

320
00:22:58,356 --> 00:22:59,941
I'm sorry for waking you.

321
00:23:00,442 --> 00:23:02,027
I said I'll leave when it's time!

322
00:23:02,110 --> 00:23:06,114
-No, that's not why we're here.
-Why do you keep bothering me?

323
00:23:07,866 --> 00:23:09,034
Hello, ma'am.

324
00:23:09,117 --> 00:23:10,243
-Hello.
-Hello.

325
00:23:10,327 --> 00:23:15,248
Oh my, I thought you were a hired thug
based on your looks.

326
00:23:16,750 --> 00:23:18,627
The hired thugs must be quite handsome.

327
00:23:19,127 --> 00:23:22,255
Hot, huh? You guys each pick
two of the most expensive ones here.

328
00:23:23,465 --> 00:23:24,299
Okay.

329
00:23:24,925 --> 00:23:26,176
Yeah. Grab a drink.

330
00:23:28,011 --> 00:23:31,556
Goodness, the expensive ones aren't there.
They're over there.

331
00:23:32,557 --> 00:23:34,351
Let's buy them all.

332
00:23:34,434 --> 00:23:38,480
-We need all of them. We'll take them all.
-Goodness, thank you so much.

333
00:23:39,814 --> 00:23:42,609
Actually, we heard
there's a great shaman around here.

334
00:23:42,692 --> 00:23:43,902
One with a daughter.

335
00:23:43,985 --> 00:23:46,196
Well…

336
00:23:46,863 --> 00:23:49,366
Oh, I don't know about "great,"

337
00:23:49,449 --> 00:23:52,536
but there was a quack shaman around.

338
00:23:53,286 --> 00:23:54,704
Do you know where her house is?

339
00:23:54,788 --> 00:23:59,584
If you go out
and keep heading up to the left,

340
00:23:59,668 --> 00:24:01,378
there's a house with a green gate.

341
00:24:01,461 --> 00:24:03,922
Oh, are you friends with her daughter?

342
00:24:06,800 --> 00:24:07,634
Well…

343
00:24:08,927 --> 00:24:11,846
I think it's been about three years
since I last saw her.

344
00:24:15,267 --> 00:24:17,978
Is this the girl you're talking about?

345
00:24:18,562 --> 00:24:19,896
Oh, that's the one.

346
00:24:20,647 --> 00:24:22,691
What was her name again?

347
00:24:22,774 --> 00:24:23,775
Hye-ryung.

348
00:24:23,858 --> 00:24:25,110
Do Hye-ryung.

349
00:24:25,193 --> 00:24:27,946
Oh, what are you talking about?

350
00:24:28,029 --> 00:24:30,365
She didn't have such a unique surname.

351
00:24:30,448 --> 00:24:32,951
-She just had a common one.
-Sorry?

352
00:24:34,869 --> 00:24:36,538
This is her.

353
00:24:37,122 --> 00:24:38,790
The shaman's daughter.

354
00:24:41,835 --> 00:24:43,378
You mean it's not her,

355
00:24:44,254 --> 00:24:45,714
but her?

356
00:24:45,797 --> 00:24:47,591
That's right. That's the one.

357
00:24:59,311 --> 00:25:00,812
Good night, ma'am.

358
00:25:03,565 --> 00:25:04,566
Hey.

359
00:25:05,066 --> 00:25:05,900
Yeah.

360
00:25:05,984 --> 00:25:08,445
Should I give the salt back
to the elderly lady?

361
00:25:08,528 --> 00:25:10,280
Se-ah, salt is expensive.

362
00:25:10,780 --> 00:25:12,866
-Huh?
-It also has a lot of uses.

363
00:25:15,827 --> 00:25:16,995
It fits perfectly.

364
00:25:17,078 --> 00:25:18,872
Let's go. Did she say it was this way?

365
00:25:19,623 --> 00:25:20,457
Yes.

366
00:25:28,465 --> 00:25:30,175
-Huh? A flag.
-The symbol!

367
00:25:39,809 --> 00:25:41,186
Wait a minute.

368
00:25:50,904 --> 00:25:51,905
Wait.

369
00:26:08,963 --> 00:26:09,964
Come in.

370
00:26:23,603 --> 00:26:25,313
The homeowner sure was a show-off.

371
00:26:25,397 --> 00:26:27,107
-Can you hand me that?
-Sure.

372
00:26:28,483 --> 00:26:30,527
This is called a dangganjiju.

373
00:26:30,610 --> 00:26:33,279
It's used to put up flags
at large temple ceremonies.

374
00:26:33,363 --> 00:26:35,532
It doesn't suit this place.

375
00:26:35,615 --> 00:26:37,033
There's blood on it.

376
00:26:40,829 --> 00:26:42,247
She wasn't a shaman

377
00:26:43,289 --> 00:26:44,332
nor a ritual master.

378
00:26:45,250 --> 00:26:46,751
What the hell?

379
00:26:54,342 --> 00:26:55,343
Stop.

380
00:26:56,636 --> 00:26:57,595
Don't move.

381
00:27:11,568 --> 00:27:12,694
-Don't move.
-Jesus.

382
00:27:13,278 --> 00:27:15,530
-You two, get closer.
-What?

383
00:27:15,613 --> 00:27:17,824
-Get closer to each other.
-Why?

384
00:27:22,287 --> 00:27:24,122
-What are you doing?
-Get really close.

385
00:27:24,831 --> 00:27:26,458
I'll tell you. Just wait.

386
00:27:35,884 --> 00:27:37,218
I'm putting up a ward

387
00:27:38,887 --> 00:27:41,681
to protect you from stray spirits.

388
00:27:50,857 --> 00:27:51,775
Stick closer.

389
00:27:51,858 --> 00:27:53,359
Stick close together.

390
00:27:53,443 --> 00:27:55,695
Do not step outside this circle, okay?

391
00:27:57,614 --> 00:27:59,616
I mean, it's so hot today.

392
00:28:00,241 --> 00:28:02,410
Did you really have to make it so small?

393
00:28:02,494 --> 00:28:06,164
Yeah. The bigger the ward is,
the weaker it gets.

394
00:28:11,711 --> 00:28:12,545
Now,

395
00:28:13,755 --> 00:28:17,550
if I shout for you to get out,
or if I don't come out in ten minutes,

396
00:28:17,634 --> 00:28:19,677
run to the car without looking back.

397
00:28:21,513 --> 00:28:22,931
Use this to open the car door,

398
00:28:23,014 --> 00:28:25,809
get inside, lock the door,
and call Haetsal on speakerphone.

399
00:28:27,143 --> 00:28:29,270
And don't come out until sunrise. Okay?

400
00:28:29,354 --> 00:28:30,897
-Yeah.
-Okay.

401
00:28:33,024 --> 00:28:34,150
What the heck is that?

402
00:28:34,776 --> 00:28:35,860
Oh God, what?

403
00:28:37,237 --> 00:28:38,071
Don't move.

404
00:28:38,154 --> 00:28:40,240
-Are you for real?
-Do not cross the line.

405
00:28:44,035 --> 00:28:45,662
What if something happens to us?

406
00:28:46,663 --> 00:28:47,956
Then just scream. Loudly.

407
00:28:48,039 --> 00:28:49,040
"Brother-in-law"!

408
00:29:14,941 --> 00:29:17,610
It sure is hot today, isn't it?

409
00:29:18,903 --> 00:29:20,655
Yeah. It really is.

410
00:29:55,440 --> 00:29:56,399
Is that blood?

411
00:30:09,662 --> 00:30:10,914
How long has it been?

412
00:30:15,001 --> 00:30:16,544
It's been three minutes.

413
00:30:17,045 --> 00:30:20,506
It's so hot and uncomfortable.
Time is dragging.

414
00:30:21,215 --> 00:30:22,133
Right?

415
00:30:22,216 --> 00:30:23,635
Yeah, that's right.

416
00:30:23,718 --> 00:30:24,677
It's uncomfortable.

417
00:30:35,146 --> 00:30:37,106
There's no shrine.

418
00:30:39,067 --> 00:30:40,068
Se-ah.

419
00:30:40,985 --> 00:30:41,986
What is it?

420
00:30:43,279 --> 00:30:44,155
Stay still.

421
00:30:47,909 --> 00:30:49,535
Why?

422
00:30:53,665 --> 00:30:54,499
I'm sorry.

423
00:31:02,423 --> 00:31:03,925
Are you out of your mind?

424
00:31:04,008 --> 00:31:06,552
-Sorry, there was a mosquito.
-Seriously…

425
00:31:11,975 --> 00:31:12,976
Ha-joon.

426
00:31:15,979 --> 00:31:17,146
Do you

427
00:31:17,897 --> 00:31:18,731
see that too?

428
00:31:20,858 --> 00:31:21,693
Huh?

429
00:33:34,700 --> 00:33:37,328
What are you doing? Where are you going?

430
00:33:38,121 --> 00:33:39,122
Where are you going?

431
00:33:55,221 --> 00:33:56,848
A painting of hell in a shrine?

432
00:33:59,767 --> 00:34:00,601
Huh?

433
00:34:05,690 --> 00:34:06,983
This feels eerie.

434
00:34:19,120 --> 00:34:20,746
What was she trying to protect?

435
00:34:38,347 --> 00:34:39,348
What the hell?

436
00:34:40,057 --> 00:34:41,142
A deolmi?

437
00:34:42,977 --> 00:34:44,187
Is this a spell?

438
00:34:48,691 --> 00:34:50,610
Is that a drawer or a door?

439
00:35:10,588 --> 00:35:11,672
Man, that got me good.

440
00:35:17,803 --> 00:35:18,804
Ha-joon.

441
00:35:22,391 --> 00:35:24,101
Don't you see it?

442
00:35:26,812 --> 00:35:27,647
Huh?

443
00:35:36,530 --> 00:35:38,741
You're scaring me. There's nothing there.

444
00:36:11,565 --> 00:36:12,566
Where are you going?

445
00:36:41,846 --> 00:36:43,139
Our school?

446
00:36:55,526 --> 00:36:56,902
Excuse me!

447
00:37:02,825 --> 00:37:03,659
Hey.

448
00:37:04,994 --> 00:37:07,955
Where were you guys?
I told you not to leave the circle.

449
00:37:08,039 --> 00:37:09,540
I saw the girl from my dream.

450
00:37:09,623 --> 00:37:11,751
I followed her and found this photo there.

451
00:37:20,426 --> 00:37:22,428
This wasn't just one person's doing.

452
00:37:23,929 --> 00:37:26,474
It seems the temple and the shrine
were mixed,

453
00:37:27,266 --> 00:37:28,351
but I'm not sure.

454
00:37:29,393 --> 00:37:32,438
With the spell they were casting
and the ruined shrine mixed up,

455
00:37:32,521 --> 00:37:36,525
I can't tell if they were cursing someone
or praying to save someone.

456
00:37:37,026 --> 00:37:38,778
And you're sure that the shaman died?

457
00:37:38,861 --> 00:37:41,906
The old lady said she saw her
being taken away after she died.

458
00:37:41,989 --> 00:37:44,450
Or should we dig into
what kind of shaman she was?

459
00:37:44,533 --> 00:37:46,952
No. Let's focus on the red phone for now.

460
00:37:47,912 --> 00:37:51,248
There's a photo with the window I saw
at the place Se-ah was taken.

461
00:37:51,791 --> 00:37:54,543
One of them must have taken a video there.

462
00:37:54,627 --> 00:37:56,796
The phone turned into a maehyung
must be there.

463
00:37:56,879 --> 00:37:57,713
All right.

464
00:37:58,255 --> 00:38:00,591
Haetsal, don't worry so much.

465
00:38:00,674 --> 00:38:03,010
I'll find it somehow.

466
00:38:08,015 --> 00:38:09,350
But how do I find it?

467
00:38:14,355 --> 00:38:16,482
It'd be nice if this were a digital photo.

468
00:38:17,733 --> 00:38:20,236
-Why's that?
-Digital photos have location data.

469
00:38:21,320 --> 00:38:23,906
Huh? Why didn't I think of that?

470
00:38:24,949 --> 00:38:25,950
-Just a sec.
-Sure.

471
00:38:26,033 --> 00:38:26,867
What?

472
00:38:27,451 --> 00:38:28,285
What is it?

473
00:38:31,747 --> 00:38:34,333
In the metadata of Geon-woo's wish video…

474
00:38:36,752 --> 00:38:39,588
See these numbers? That's the GPS data.

475
00:38:39,672 --> 00:38:43,008
If you look up these numbers,
it shows you where the video was taken.

476
00:38:43,092 --> 00:38:44,718
Judging by the Girigo code,

477
00:38:44,802 --> 00:38:47,263
all the videos
were likely uploaded to the server.

478
00:38:47,346 --> 00:38:51,350
So we just need to download the video
from the server and check the GPS data?

479
00:38:51,434 --> 00:38:52,268
Yeah.

480
00:38:53,602 --> 00:38:56,480
You sure are amazing, brother-in-law.
Seriously amazing.

481
00:39:00,443 --> 00:39:02,987
This only lets devices registered
on the server log in.

482
00:39:03,737 --> 00:39:06,198
Wait! I've seen this screen before.

483
00:39:07,116 --> 00:39:08,200
Huh?

484
00:39:08,284 --> 00:39:09,201
Where?

485
00:39:11,996 --> 00:39:13,539
ADMIN ID
4BONG

486
00:39:13,622 --> 00:39:15,583
On Coach Song's computer.

487
00:39:35,352 --> 00:39:36,854
Is someone still here?

488
00:39:39,565 --> 00:39:41,275
Coach Song will be coming out soon.

489
00:39:41,775 --> 00:39:43,402
She's always the last to leave.

490
00:39:43,486 --> 00:39:46,155
So there won't be anyone at school
once Coach Song leaves?

491
00:39:46,238 --> 00:39:47,114
Yes.

492
00:39:47,198 --> 00:39:48,282
What about the CCTVs?

493
00:39:48,365 --> 00:39:49,408
There's a way.

494
00:39:51,994 --> 00:39:52,995
Se-ah.

495
00:39:53,746 --> 00:39:55,289
The ghost you said you saw today,

496
00:39:55,372 --> 00:39:57,791
can you tell who she is in this photo?

497
00:39:58,959 --> 00:40:02,755
No. I don't know who she is,
but I think she's trying to help me.

498
00:40:03,422 --> 00:40:04,548
She found this for me.

499
00:40:09,929 --> 00:40:12,014
Let's not jump to conclusions so easily.

500
00:40:12,806 --> 00:40:15,184
She might be slowly trying to reel us in.

501
00:40:16,101 --> 00:40:17,186
Most ghosts do that.

502
00:40:17,269 --> 00:40:19,480
Then shouldn't we come up with a plan?

503
00:40:19,563 --> 00:40:21,273
We do have a plan.

504
00:40:21,357 --> 00:40:22,525
Me and your sister.

505
00:40:23,692 --> 00:40:25,903
Big talk usually ends in a big stumble.

506
00:40:28,614 --> 00:40:29,907
Ha-joon.

507
00:40:29,990 --> 00:40:32,117
-Come on, let's go.
-Okay.

508
00:40:32,618 --> 00:40:33,744
Just the two of you?

509
00:40:35,579 --> 00:40:37,915
It's our school.
It'll be quickest that way.

510
00:40:37,998 --> 00:40:39,750
Even if we're caught, it's simpler.

511
00:40:39,833 --> 00:40:40,751
Hold on.

512
00:40:47,883 --> 00:40:48,759
But be quick.

513
00:40:48,842 --> 00:40:49,677
Okay.

514
00:40:50,678 --> 00:40:51,804
And be careful.

515
00:40:51,887 --> 00:40:52,721
Okay.

516
00:41:13,993 --> 00:41:16,370
How did you know
there was a hole in the fence here?

517
00:41:17,371 --> 00:41:18,539
I'm the one who made it.

518
00:41:18,622 --> 00:41:19,498
What for?

519
00:41:19,582 --> 00:41:20,916
To make the national team.

520
00:41:21,417 --> 00:41:23,502
I wanted to practice more in secret.

521
00:41:27,089 --> 00:41:28,132
Let's go.

522
00:41:28,215 --> 00:41:29,216
Okay.

523
00:41:36,974 --> 00:41:38,183
One, two, three, four.

524
00:41:39,184 --> 00:41:40,227
That's the code?

525
00:41:40,311 --> 00:41:43,105
Yeah. Our coach uses it for everything.

526
00:41:43,188 --> 00:41:44,440
They're all the same.

527
00:41:50,529 --> 00:41:51,363
1, 2, 3, 4.

528
00:41:54,199 --> 00:41:55,576
Thank you.

529
00:41:56,619 --> 00:41:58,704
YOUTH SMARTPHONE APP DEVELOPMENT CONTEST
GIRIGO

530
00:42:00,039 --> 00:42:01,290
GIRIGO/VIDEO

531
00:42:04,293 --> 00:42:05,127
